data.output: It was a sunny day and little Mia's favourite place to play was next to the old pink water pump hidden in the wildflowers at her grandma's house. At only 6 years old, she didn't quite know what it was but had painted, decorated and pretended it was magic for as long as she could remember. Her grandma would tell her of the days when the big petrol and diesel trucks would come rolling through the town but Mia wasn't interested in the history, only in the fantasy worlds she could create in her beautiful hideout.

Stamp, stamp, stamp. All day Lucy would sit at her little bank desk stamping approvals on loans, mortgages and other banking products. At the end of each day, she would take the letters over to Michael to send to clients. Michael was Lucy's crush and had been since she started at the company 6 years ago. Today however, was different, today she would tell him how she felt.

As the organ played its first notes, Becky stood in front of the grand doors, her empire-waist wedding dress shimmering in the sunlight. The dress had been passed down for generations and here she was about to comply with her long standing family traditions. On the other side of the door stood all her family and friends, waiting for her to marry the love of her life.

Princess Ella sat by her window, watching the gloom of the forest fade as the sun rose over the castle grounds. Her loyal horse, Starlight, waited patiently for her, eager for their morning ride. Ella had dreamed of riding beyond her kingdom, where legends spoke of a hidden realm that didn't yet exist on any map. The only payment required to enter was a heart full of courage and a will to succeed, two things Ella had by the bucketful.
